  "body": "- [x] I've asked for help in the [Truffle Gitter](http://gitter.im/Consensys/truffle) before filing this issue.\r\n\r\n---------------------------\r\n\r\nHey folks! Fairly new to Truffle. Thanks for this great framework. I'm happy to try to solve this issue w/ a PR but will likely need some guidance.\r\n\r\n## Issue\r\n\r\nThe `truffle create contract` command outputs a .sol file blueprint with a different solidity compiler version vs. what `truffle version` outputs and/or what is specified in truffle-config.js.\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\nInit a new truffle project and create a contract:\r\n`$ mkdir truffle-test && cd truffle-test`\r\n`$ truffle init`\r\n`$ truffle create contract MyContract`\r\n\r\nLooking at the MyContract.sol code...\r\n```\r\npragma solidity ^0.4.22;\r\n\r\ncontract MyContract {\r\n  constructor() public {\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\n\r\nI expected the contract blueprint to use solidity ^0.5.1, given that is the result when running `truffle version`. I tried editing the compiler configuration in truffle-config.js:\r\n```\r\ncompilers: {\r\n  solc: {\r\n    version: '0.5.1'\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n```\r\nBue re-running the `truffle create contract` command yielded the same result.\r\n\r\n## Actual Results\r\n\r\nThe contract blueprint uses solidity ^0.4.22. Contents of MyContract.sol:\r\n```\r\npragma solidity ^0.4.22;\r\n\r\ncontract MyContract {\r\n  constructor() public {\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Operating System: macOS Mojave 10.14.2\r\n* Ethereum client: N/A\r\n* Truffle version (`truffle version`):\r\n```\r\n$ truffle version\r\nTruffle v5.0.1 (core: 5.0.1)\r\nSolidity - 0.5.1 (solc-js)\r\nNode v10.13.0\r\n```\r\n* node version (`node --version`):\r\n```\r\n$ node --version\r\nv10.13.0\r\n```\r\n* npm version (`npm --version`): \r\n```\r\n$ npm --version\r\n6.4.1\r\n```\r\n",
